The paper proposes a general framework for interactively learning models, which is a topic that falls under the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The framework is based on a graph representation, which involves algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) and computational complexity (cs.CC). The paper also discusses interactive clustering, which is a topic in the social and information networks (cs.SI) sub-category.
